Nice, thank you for sharing this.

Will this force the shutdown if Heritrix becomes unresponsive. Maybe a Bash script that waits X seconds for the process to terminate, and if it doesn&#39;t to then kill it.

I think I have a sample Bash script somewhere that does this on another server I work with.

Briggs &lt;acidbriggs@...&gt; wrote:                               So, I looked at how I would shutdown my instance via the command line,
 it would go like this:

 java -jar cmdline-jmxclient-0.10.5.jar controlRole:admin
 localhost:8849 org.archive.crawler:jmxport=8849,name=Heritrix,type=CrawlService,guiport=8080,host=dev-odc-006
 shutdown

 so you need modify that to work for you:

 java -jar cmdline-jmxclient-0.10.5.jar controlRole:&lt;your_password&gt;
 &lt;your_machine&gt;:&lt;your_port&gt; &lt;your_heritrix_mbean&gt; shutdown

 On Dec 18, 2007 12:28 PM, Briggs &lt;acidbriggs@...&gt; wrote:
 &gt; The only way i know of doing it is using the MBeans that get deployed.
 &gt;
 &gt; You can use the cmdline-jmxclient-0.10.5.jar int the bin directory of
 &gt; heritrix to call these beans. But, you&#39;ll have to do the research on
 &gt; which bean/method to call to shut it down as I haven&#39;t looked.  But,
 &gt; you can try opening up the JConsole and looking at the beans.
 &gt;
